cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper involves the application of machine learning techniques to remote sensing data for the detection and prediction of harmful algal blooms. The use of spatiotemporal datacube structures and novel machine learning methods suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of a prediction system also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves the analysis of data from the Arabian Gulf, suggesting a possible focus on graphics (cs.GR) or information retrieval (cs.IR) for the analysis of this data.
